In this article, the importance of financial independence and the need for improved financial capabilities among Americans are emphasized. The Tax Cuts and Jobs Act of 2017 is highlighted as a means to provide more opportunities for Americans to invest and save their money. The article also mentions the efforts of the Department of the Treasury to enhance financial education and make it more effective. The goal is to empower Americans to make informed financial decisions, save for retirement, and build individual wealth. The article concludes by inviting families, communities, schools, employers, and other institutions to join in promoting financial literacy during National Financial Capability Month.